Stakeholders have called for investment in women football as a viable means of empowering the girl-child through sports participation. The call was made at the maiden edition of the Afusat Olabimpe Abiodun Female Gold Cup in Ikorodu, Lagos. The tournament which began on Jan. 23 drew female teams from all parts of the state in a battle for the title.   Ziyech strike gives Chelsea victory at Crystal Palace     Burnley beat Brighton to move off bottom     Salah, Mane, Diaz deliver as Liverpool keep pressure on…   The final held on Feb. 13 at Strong Towers School Sports Field, Ikorodu,  was a showdown between Prince Kazeem Eletu Queens of Ikorodu and Papa Soccer Academy of Epe. The fierce encounter was decided on penalties after both sides battled to 1:1 draw at full time. The penalty shoot out led to the emergence of Kazeem Eletu Queens as champion of the tournament. - Advertisement - Speaking at the closing ceremony, Director-General, Lagos State Sports Commission, Oluwatoyin Bolowotan, said that the tournament was organised to promote the development of the girl-child. Bolowotan expressed the hope that the competition would promote growth of female football, adding that the competition would encourage more girl-child to venture into sports. SPONSORED